/* Create a function that takes a 2D array as input, where each inner array represents a row of data. Dynamically create an HTML table, populating it with the data from the 2D array.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Dynamic Table Creation</title>
</head>
<body>
  <div id="table-container"></div>
  <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html> */

/* 
Hints:
Create a <table> element using document.createElement("table").
Create <tr> and <td> elements for each row and cell, respectively.
Set the textContent of each <td> element to the corresponding data value.
Append the <td> elements to the <tr> elements, and then append the <tr> elements to the <table> element.
Finally, append the <table> element to the specified container. */



***
const tableData = ["Name", "Age", "Birthday", "Country"];

function createTable() {
  const table = document.createElement("table");
  const container = document.getElementById("table-container");

  for (let i = 0; i < tableData.length; i++) {
    const tr = document.createElement("tr");
    const td = document.createElement("td");
    td.textContent = tableData[i];
    tr.appendChild(td);
    table.appendChild(tr);
  }

  container.appendChild(table);
}

createTable();
***



/*
Explanation:
Create table and container reference: We create a new table element and get a reference to the container element.
Iterate over data: We iterate over the tableData array.
Create row and cell: For each iteration, we create a new tr (table row) and td (table cell) element.
Set cell content: We set the textContent of the td element to the current data value.
Append cell to row: We append the td element to the tr element.
Append row to table: We append the tr element to the table element.
Append table to container: Finally, we append the table element to the container element. */
